    {
      "id": "5e1c8a32-8a62-41fb-bfa6-049993db0bc2",
      "type": "paragraph",
      "text": "The authors validate their hypothesis that integrating semantic meaning to knowledge tracing improves the current state of the art for these methods, as indicated by the fact that LKT outperforms other KT models on the benchmark datasets. Also, this semantic knowledge seems to be a viable solution to address the cold-start problem often found in KT tasks. Also, the model is argued to be more interpretable due to its use of rich text data. ",
      "raw": {
        "object": "block",
        "id": "5e1c8a32-8a62-41fb-bfa6-049993db0bc2",
        "parent": {
          "type": "page_id",
